<div class="about">
    <h1>About</h1>
    <p>The Hallway Track is a weekly curated link roundup covering how AI is affecting the practice of science. Not the hype, not the benchmarks. The actual changes to how research gets done. What was built, what was published, what it means for working researchers.</p>

    <p>The beat covers AI agents for literature review, automated research pipelines, infrastructure for AI-assisted science, accountability and authorship questions, and changes to peer review. It does not cover model benchmarks, frontier lab announcements, or general AI product news.</p>

    <p>Links are gathered with the help of automated source scanning. The selection and commentary are by a human, Leo Torres, researcher in network science and director of <a href="https://aris.pub">The Aris Program</a>.</p>

    <p>The Hallway Track is part of <a href="https://aris.pub">The Aris Program</a>, an initiative building web-native infrastructure for academic publishing.</p>
</div>
